properties.areaDesc: East Slopes of the Washington Cascades
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 6 at 4:33AM PST until January 6 at 1:00PM PST by NWS Pendleton OR
properties.description:
...Snow will continue in the Cascades and Blue Mountains today...

.Pacific moisture continues to overspread the region and bring
snow to the Cascades. Several more inches of snow will fall on
Snoqualmie and White Passes today. Snow accumulations will be in
feet on area mountains. Snow is also expected in the Blue Mtns
where 2 to 10 inches are expected. Breezy winds could lead to
areas of blowing and drifting snow.

* WHAT...Snow below 3000 feet. Additional snow accumulations of up
to 7 inches. Winds will be breezy, especially on exposed areas,
and may lead to blowing or drifting snow.

* WHERE...East Slopes of the Washington Cascades including
Snoqualmie and White Passes.

* WHEN...Until 1 PM PST this afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Travel may be difficult over Snoqualmie and White
Passes.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1 or visiting Washington DOT online.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1 PM PST THIS AFTERNOON BELOW 3000 FEET
